devdoc.details: ensure usingAugur is set to false upon local testing and true on kovan or mainnet

_collectRent(uint256).details: also calculates and updates how long the current user has held the token for

collectRentAllTokens().details: makes it easy for me to call whenever I want to keep people paying their rent

exit(uint256).details: do not need to be the current owner

liveDepositAbleToWithdraw(uint256).return: how much the current owner has deposited

rentOwed(uint256).details: called in collectRent function, and various other view functions

step1checkMarketsResolved(uint256,bool).details: these five functions are done seperately because if they were done at once, the gas cost could easily cross the block limitcan be called by anyone can be called multiple times, but only once after markets have indeed resolvedthe two arguments passed are for testing only

step2getLoopsRequired().details: this function gets the required number of loops needed in the returnDeposits and returnAllFunds functions. We get it once only to save gas. can be called by anyone, but only once

step3returnDeposits(uint256).details: the _numberOfLoopsToDo argument allows this function to be completed over multiple txs, protecting against denial of service attackstrying to return all deposits to all users at once could easily hit the block limitcan be called by anyone, but only once (all the way through)

step4sellCompleteSetsAndPayAndrew().details: gets funds back from Augur, gets the available funds for distribution and pays me my 1%can be called by anyone, but only once

step5complete(uint256).details: can be called by anyone, but only once (all the way through)_numberOfLoopsToDo and _hardCodedWinner are testing variables only

userDepositAbleToWithdraw(uint256).return: how much the current user has deposited

withdrawDeposit(uint256,uint256).details: do not need to be the current owner

_collectRent(uint256).notice: collects rent for a specific token

changePrice(uint256,uint256).notice: increase the price of an existing rental

collectRentAllTokens().notice: /////////// ORDINARY COURSE OF BUSINESS FUNCTIONS //////////////collects rent for all tokens

depositDai(uint256,uint256).notice: add new dai deposit to an existing rental

step1BemergencyExit().notice: emergency function in case the augur markets never resolve for whatever reasonreturns all funds to all userscan only be called 6 months after augur markets should have ended

step1CcircuitBreaker().notice: Same as above, except that only I can call it, and I can call it whenever

step1checkMarketsResolved(uint256,bool).notice: /////////// MARKET RESOLUTION FUNCTIONS ////////////// the first of five functions which must be called, one after the other, to conclude the competitionthis function checks whether the Augur markets have resolved, and if yes, whether they resolved correct or not

step2getLoopsRequired().notice: the second of five functions which must be called, one after the other, to conclude the competition

step3returnDeposits(uint256).notice: the third of five functions which must be called, one after the other, to conclude the competitionreturns unused deposits to all users

step4sellCompleteSetsAndPayAndrew().notice: the fourth of five functions which must be called, one after the other, to conclude the competition

step5complete(uint256).notice: the final of five functions which must be called, one after the other, to conclude the competitiondetermines whether markets resolved correctly- if yes, payout winnings, if not, return all funds
